    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT140-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">poruḷavayiṟ pirintaviṭattu nī āṟṟukiṉṟilai eṉṟa tōḻikkut talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Uttered by HER to the confidante who had said “you have not got the strength”, when [he] separated for the sake of wealth.</p>
          </div>


        <div xml:id="KT140">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                vētiṉa verini ṉōti mutupōt</l>
<l>                tāṟuceṉ mākkaḷ puṭkoḷap poruntuñ</l>
<l>                curaṉē ceṉṟaṉar kātala ruraṉaḻin</l>
<l>                tīṅkiyāṉ ṟāṅkiya vevvam</l>
<l>                yāṅkaṟin taṉṟiv vaḻuṅka lūrē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
           <l>Into the desert the lover has gone,</l>
           <l rend="indent">which is apt to make people walking the route take as an omen</l>
           <l rend="indent">the old male of the chameleon with [its] saw-back.</l>
           <l>What does this noisy village know<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">aṟintaṉṟu</term>: what is achieved here by the p.a.? "What has the village understood?" Or a real question: "How has this noisy village got knowledge of my trouble?"</note></l>
           <l rend="indent">of the trouble I endured here, [my] strength perished?</l>
        

            </lg>
        </div>
